* Differential Amplifier (Long-Tail Pair)
*
* Topology:
*   VCC в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ
*           в”Ӯ                  в”Ӯ
*          RL1                RL2
*           в”Ӯ                  в”Ӯ
*         col1в”Җв”ҖCoutв”Җв”Җout    col2
*           в”Ӯ                  в”Ӯ
*          Q1                 Q2
*           в”Ӯ                  в”Ӯ
*        base1              base2
*           в”Ӯ                  в”Ӯ
*    Cin_pв”Җв”Җв”ҳ                  в””в”Җв”ҖCin_n
*           в”Ӯ                  в”Ӯ
*        emit1              emit2
*           в”Ӯ                  в”Ӯ
*      в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ        в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
*     Ce1       RE1      Ce2       RE2
*      в”Ӯ         в”Ӯ        в”Ӯ         в”Ӯ
*     GND      tail      GND      tail
*                 в”Ӯ
*              R_tail
*                 в”Ӯ
*               VEE
*
* Design considerations:
*   - Ce1/Ce2 bypass RE1/RE2 at AC, restoring high differential gain
*   - Without bypass caps, gain = R_L / (2Г—R_E + r_e) which can be < 1
*     for large R_E values in the registry (100О© to 2kО©)
*   - With bypass caps, AC gain вүҲ gm Г— R_L (much higher)
*   - R_E still provides DC degeneration for bias stability
*   - R_tail sets tail current: I_tail вүҲ (V_E - VEE) / R_tail
*
* Differential AC gain вүҲ gm Г— R_L = (I_C / V_T) Г— R_L
* At I_C = 1mA, gm = 40mS, with R_L = 5kО©: gain = 200 V/V вүҲ 46 dB

******** SUPPLIES ********
VCC vcc 0 DC 12
VEE 0 vee DC 12

******** INPUT SOURCES ********
* Differential: AC on positive input, negative input at AC ground
Vsig_p sig_p 0 DC 0 AC 1
Vsig_n sig_n 0 DC 0 AC 0

* Source impedances
Rs_p sig_p in_p 600
Rs_n sig_n in_n 600

******** INPUT COUPLING ********
Cin_p in_p base1 1u
Cin_n in_n base2 1u

******** BIAS NETWORK ********
* Voltage divider sets quiescent base voltage
* V_base вүҲ VCC Г— 100k/(100k+100k) = 6V (relative to ground)
* V_emitter вүҲ 5.3V, so V_E - VEE = 5.3 - (-12) = 17.3V
* I_tail = 17.3V / R_tail
Rb1_q1 vcc base1 100k
Rb2_q1 base1 0 100k
Rb1_q2 vcc base2 100k
Rb2_q2 base2 0 100k

******** DIFFERENTIAL PAIR ********
Q1 col1 base1 emit1 QNPN
Q2 col2 base2 emit2 QNPN

******** EMITTER NETWORK ********
* R_E provides DC degeneration for bias stability and CMRR
* Ce bypasses R_E at AC for maximum differential gain
* Without Ce, gain is severely limited by R_E (registry: 100-2000О©)
RE1 emit1 tail {RE_VAL}
Ce1 emit1 tail 47u
RE2 emit2 tail {RE_VAL}
Ce2 emit2 tail 47u

******** TAIL CURRENT SOURCE ********
Rtail tail vee {RTAIL_VAL}

******** COLLECTOR LOADS ********
RL1 vcc col1 {RL_VAL}
RL2 vcc col2 {RL_VAL}

******** OUTPUT COUPLING ********
Cout col1 out 1u
Rload out 0 10k

******** TRANSISTOR MODEL ********
.model QNPN NPN (IS=6.7e-15 BF=200 VAF=100
+                RB=10 RC=1 RE=0.5
+                CJE=18p VJE=0.7  MJE=0.33 TF=300p
+                CJC=4p  VJC=0.75 MJC=0.33 TR=4n
+                XTB=1.5 EG=1.11  XTI=3)

******** ANALYSIS ********
.ac dec 100 10 500Meg

******** EXPORT DATA ********
.control
run
set filetype=ascii
wrdata ngspice_simulation_output.txt frequency v(out)
.endc

.end
